div1.p:
The Prisoner called Henry Street, who had known him seven years;
Edward Perry
one year;
Joseph Yeoman
three years;
Charles Powley
and
John Beale
five years, who all gave him a good character.

The prisoner called
William Young
, who keeps a boarding school at Kensington, with when he had lived as an assistant four years, who deposed, that he behaved with the greatest properties and decorum, and was a very worthy by assistant,
Thomas Home
, who has known him three years;
Catherine Purser
, between four and five years;
Samuel Archibald
, three years;
Robert Pezar
, five or six years;
Daniel Lee
, four or five years; Mr. Rowley, three or four years; and John Wickstead, three years; several of whom had children now under his care; and all gave him the best of characters.
